━━━ DECOMPOSING THE ACTION INTO REQUIREMENTS ━━━
Instead of writing one run-on action description, break the action down into the distinct
*requirements* it must satisfy — the underlying needs, not the wording. For each requirement,
decide:
- Is there genuinely only ONE valid way to satisfy it? → mark it "mandatory": true and give
  exactly ONE option. Do not mark something mandatory just because it's important — only when
  no real alternative approach exists. Some actions may have ZERO mandatory requirements.
- Are there multiple legitimate ways to satisfy it (different methods, tools, or approaches)?
  → mark it "mandatory": false and give 2 to 5 options that are *meaningfully different* from
  each other — not the same instruction reworded three times. The user reviewing this action
  may select more than one option if several genuinely apply together.

The number of requirements is not fixed — a narrow containment action might have only 1,
a systemic preventive action might have 4 or 5. Decide based on what this specific action
actually needs, don't force a template count.

Worked example (Corrective action — failed crane wire rope):
{
  "type": "Corrective",
  "title": "Replace and prevent recurrence of failed crane wire rope",
  "requirements": [
    {
      "label": "Eliminate the immediate hazard",
      "mandatory": true,
      "options": [
        {"text": "Replace the failed wire rope on Overhead Crane OCR-CHN-01 with a manufacturer-specified ISO 4309 compliant grade."}
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Catch this failure mode before it recurs",
      "mandatory": false,
      "options": [
        {"text": "Update the crane's PM card to check strand count via bore gauge per ISO 4309 Table 6."},
        {"text": "Add a quarterly third-party NDT (non-destructive testing) inspection of all wire ropes."},
        {"text": "Install a wire-rope condition-monitoring sensor on the crane."}
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "Confirm the fix before resuming operation",
      "mandatory": true,
      "options": [
        {"text": "Verify the new rope is installed and the work order is recorded before the next scheduled lift."}
      ]
    }
  ],
  "linked_root_cause": "The PM programme specified visual inspection only, with no bore gauge method or ISO 4309 discard criteria defined.",
  "rationale": "Replacing the rope removes the immediate hazard; the PM card update closes the inspection-method gap that let it fail undetected."
}

━━━ OUTPUT INSTRUCTIONS ━━━
Return a JSON array of exactly {{ num_actions }} action object(s). Each object must follow this schema:

{
  "type": "{{ action_type }}",
  "title": "<concise action title, max 15 words>",
  "requirements": [
    {
      "label": "<the underlying need this requirement addresses>",
      "mandatory": true | false,
      "options": [
        {"text": "<one concrete way to satisfy this requirement>"}
      ]
    }
  ],
  "linked_root_cause": "<copy the root cause statement verbatim or the closest match from context>",
  "rationale": "<1-2 concise sentences on why this action addresses the root cause — not an essay>"
}

Rules:
- Every field is required.
- requirements must have at least 1 entry.
- A requirement with "mandatory": true must have exactly 1 option.
- A requirement with "mandatory": false must have 2 to 5 options, each a meaningfully different approach.
- linked_root_cause must come from the CAPA context above — do not hallucinate.
- rationale: 1-2 sentences, not a paragraph.
- Return ONLY the JSON array. No markdown, no explanation.
